{
    "name": "Serpentfolk Illusionist",
    "type": "monster",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Tactics",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>During Combat</b> A serpentfolk illusionist seeks to deceive opponents with spells until it can debilitate them with <i>blindness/deafness</i>, <i>color spray</i>, or a venomous bite enhanced with <i>pernicious poison</i>. Otherwise, it attacks with its wand or uses <i>suggestion</i> and <i>dominate person</i> to turn enemies into allies."
        },
        {
            "name": "Ecology",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Environment</b> any land (usually jungles or underground)"
        },
        {
            "name": "Special Abilities",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "<b>Poison (Ex)</b> Bite\u2014injury; <i>save </i>Fort DC 17; <i>frequency </i>1/round for 6 rounds; <i>effect </i>1d2 Str; <i>cure </i>2 saves. The save DC is Constitution-based."
        },
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "A serpentfolk illusionist has greatly enhanced its racial gifts for deception with decades of intensive arcane study. On the surface world, it is often the leader of a group of serpentfolk or a cult of lesser reptilian humanoids."
        }
    ],
